## Multi-tenancy rule
Every database query that touches business data **must** filter by `businessId`. Never return cross-tenant data. The `businessId` is always derived from the authenticated user ‚Äî never from a request body or query param.

## Roles
`SUPER_ADMIN` ¬∑ `BUSINESS_ADMIN` ¬∑ `STAFF` ‚Äî defined in `UserRole` Prisma enum. UI gated via `/me/ui` endpoint.

## Auth flow
JWT access token (short-lived) + refresh token stored in `RefreshToken` table with indexed `tokenPrefix` (first 8 chars) for O(1) lookup. Mobile signup uses OTP (dev stub: `1234`). Password login for admin/staff. Global rate limit: 60 req/min via `ThrottlerModule`.

## Dynamic content (SiteContent)
All user-facing text (landing page, SEO metadata, WhatsApp message templates, city pages, onboarding text) is stored in the `SiteContent` model. Keys use dotted namespaces: `landing.hero.title`, `seo.landing.description`, `wa.booking_confirm`. Editable by Super Admin at `/app/superadmin/content`. Redis cached for 5 minutes ‚Äî invalidated on update.

## WhatsApp automation (BullMQ)
- `booking_confirm` ‚Äî enqueued immediately when appointment status ‚Üí CONFIRMED
- `reminder_24h` ‚Äî enqueued at appointment creation, delayed to `startAt ‚àí 24h`
- `post_visit` ‚Äî enqueued when status ‚Üí COMPLETED, delayed 24h
- `inactive_recovery` ‚Äî scaffolded; requires a cron to trigger
- All message templates are fetched from `SiteContent` DB at job processing time (supports Super Admin edits without redeploy)

## Redis / graceful degradation
- `REDIS_URL` in production currently points to localhost (placeholder) ‚Äî slot lock and BullMQ degrade gracefully
- Slot lock: if Redis is unavailable `redisAvailable=false` ‚Üí skips lock, proceeds with Prisma TX only
- SiteContent caching: try/catch around all Redis ops ‚Üí falls back to DB query
- BullMQ queue `add()` calls: all wrapped in try/catch ‚Üí non-fatal, reminders skipped if Redis down

